						               													<description>The cure for a broken heart is... Revenge&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Jane Austen&amp;rsquo;s Revenge is an expansion for Jane Austen&amp;rsquo;s Matchmaker Chapter Two. Nothing spices up a good romance like a dash of bitterness and betrayal.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;As one of Society&amp;rsquo;s premier matchmakers, your goal remains the same &amp;ndash; to gain the most Prestige &amp;ndash; but you must also settle scores with your rivals to finish the game holding as few Grudges as possible.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Grudge cards&amp;#10;Each player starts the game with 2 Grudge cards. During play you draw Grudge cards whenever someone does something to vex you &amp;ndash; such as declining your proposal. Grudge cards can be played during the game to hurt your rivals. Each Grudge card in your hand subtracts 5 Prestige from your final score. So getting even is always preferable to staying mad.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A Change of Heart card can be played when you propose a match to alter two of your character&amp;rsquo;s Traits &amp;ndash; making one better and the other worse.&amp;#10;Duel&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Some grudges can only be settled with a Duel. In polite society this may mean a war of words, a sword fight, pistols at dawn, or even a horse race!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Turmoil cards potentially affect everyone but, if played cleverly, can mitigate the effects on your characters while making your rivals suffer.&amp;#10;Lady Susan&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A marriage to the beautiful and capricious Lady Susan is apt to be short and vexatious. A quick divorce later, and she&amp;rsquo;s back in the game!&amp;#10;Patronage&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If things aren&amp;rsquo;t going your way, you can ask an influential patron to change your luck! If you roll the Trait on the card you may change it to your patron&amp;rsquo;s preferred Trait instead.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
